  "texts": [
    "For example, legit researchers obtain or recover the whole or partial genomic sequence of a target individual (privacy violation through reference), link the sequence to a target individual (ie, reidentifying), and identify the group of interest of a target individual (privacy violation through membership reference) when processing data from multiple sources.",
    "In addition, the growth of synthetic medical data in health AI systems raises concerns about the vulnerabilities of such systems and the challenges of the current regulations and policies.Table 2 summarizes the data sources and security or privacy threats for each type of generative AI in health care in the data collection and processing phase.",
    "Again, it should be noted that although all AI and machine learning systems face many similar threats, as listed in Table 2, generative AI amplifies them because of its generating nature and data source volume and complexity.",
    "For example, generative medical research AI may update knowledge and literature databases with \"wrong inputs\" based on wrong findings in these databases or with synthesized but hallucinated findings.",
    "Similarly, generative virtual health assistants may put dangerous advice into knowledge databases based on erroneous data from sources or again put synthesized but hallucinated advice into such databases."
